text:
I’m fine with walkers that flip into creatures, but I feel like they would at least need two abilities for interesting gameplay purposes. Just one ability and then immediately flipping almost feels like putting Flash on a sorcery. 

I’m not opposed to reverse flip walkers, it just seems like a weird hoop to jump through from a design perspective especially if there isn’t any gameplay choice involved. They’d feel more like etb creatures or enchantments rather than walkers if there was only one ability.
tails
Thank you, Slackbot
I'm down with that. Maybe both abilities (a + and a -) still make it transform, and then the creature has that many +1/+1 counters.
That could be cool, right?
As long as there is some kind of choice involved, I’d be happy.
Granted, this makes the complexity of this set go *through the roof*.

100%. I’m really interested in seeing how they’re going to pull this off. It must take a lot of money and resources to put a set like this together.

I know they’ve done the Innistrad sets with a bunch of flip cards, but if all the walkers flip, that’s a lot of high priced art that they have to commission
